[SN]TITLE[SN]
100 Women 2015: the female farmers unable to own their land

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
More than a third of the world's workforce works in agriculture and in developing countries, and women make up 43% of the workforce.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
27 November 2015 Last updated at 09:08 GMT
But they comprise less than a fifth of landholders.
Access to secure tenure and ownership of land is harder for women than men, and there is an imbalance in yields produced by male and female farmers because they lack equal access to resources such as seeds.
